REFERRED TO OUTPATIENT COMPETENCY RESTORATION PROGRAM (OCRP)

Defendant Zaheim Humphrey appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Robert Lee Taylor appeared in court on behalf of  Attorney Amanda Kremer for Zaheim Humphrey.  Attorney Eric Bashirian appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Doctor's Report Return. Court reviewed Report dated September 13, 2022 and submitted by Dr. Jenna Niess. Parties did not challenge the report. Court found that at the present time, Defendant lacks substantial mental capacity to understand the proceedings against him and assist in his own defense, but he is likely to be restored to competency with restorative treatment. Court ordered proceeding suspended and ordered restorative treatment to continue at Milwaukee County Jail. 

Court ordered case adjourned for Doctor's Report Return, Branch 46. Doctor's Report Return scheduled for December 2, 2022 at 10:00 pm. Hearing will be held via Zoom Video Conference. Defendant will appear via Zoom Video Conference.
-dated September 13, 2022 and submitted by Dr. Jenna Niess; received, filed, and forwarded to the Judge for review.

Case set for a preliminary hearing. Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed. Doctor's Report Return scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Case in Court for an Order to Show Cause hearing. Parties appeared in Room 113 of the Safety Building. Public Defender's Office has NOT been able to appoint counsel for Defendant.
